value.value: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoanterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 148 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

definition.value: The GABAergic neurotransmitter was assessed by labelling cells with an antibody against GABA (Chin et al., 2014).

value.value: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoanterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 40 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

definition.value: The GABAergic neurotransmitter was assessed by labelling cells with an antibody against GABA (Chin et al., 2014).

value.value: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoanterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 110 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

definition.value: The GABAergic neurotransmitter was assessed by labelling cells with an antibody against GABA (Chin et al., 2014).

value.value: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the most dorsal region of the M6 layer, covering around 51 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

definition.value: The GABAergic neurotransmitter was assessed by labelling cells with an antibody against GABA (Chin et al., 2014).

value.value: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the dorsoposterior region of the M6 layer, covering around 54 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

definition.value: The GABAergic neurotransmitter was assessed by labelling cells with an antibody against GABA (Chin et al., 2014).

value.value: Non-directional local neuron that is restricted to layer 6 of the medulla. Its soma is in the dorsal region of the lateral cell body rind. This neuron arborizes in the posterior region of the M6 layer, extending anterioposteriorly, covering around 74 columns. It is a GABAergic neuron.

definition.value: The GABAergic neurotransmitter was assessed by labelling cells with an antibody against GABA (Chin et al., 2014).

label.value: gustatory receptor neuron of terminal organ distal group

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron whose dendrites innervate the terminal organ on the surface of the larval head and whose soma is located in the terminal organ ganglion (terminal organ distal group) (Rist and Thum, 2017). The axons of these neurons project via the maxillary nerve (Python and Stocker, 2002) into area 4 of the subesophageal ganglion. There are 11 of these neurons on each side (Rist and Thum, 2017).

label.value: adult ventral nerve cord cell body rind

value.value: Superficial layer of the adult ventral nerve cord, composed of glia and the cell bodies of neurons (soma).

label.value: cell body rind of adult prothoracic neuromere

value.value: Region of the adult ventral nerve cord cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the prothoracic neuromere.

label.value: cell body rind of adult mesothoracic neuromere

value.value: Region of the adult ventral nerve cord cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the mesothoracic neuromere.

label.value: cell body rind of adult metathoracic neuromere

value.value: Region of the adult ventral nerve cord cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the metathoracic neuromere.

label.value: cell body rind of adult abdominal neuromere

value.value: Region of the adult ventral nerve cord cell body rind that overlies the neuropil of the abdominal neuromere.

Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located between the metathoracic and abdominal neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010). It has arborization in the dorsal anterior of metathoracic neuromere and a branch that leaves the ventral nerve cord (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: No female examples shown by Yu et al. (2010).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal abdominal segment. It projects anteriorly along the midline, forming arbors in the pro- and mesothoracic segments, close to the terminals of the leg sensory afferents. It also arborizes in the brain.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located laterally on the dorsal abdominal neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects along the ventral midline forming arbors in the pro- and mesothoracic segments close to the terminals of the leg sensory afferents (Yu et al., 2010). It has an ascending projection (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: No female examples shown by Yu et al. (2010).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal abdominal segment, between the metathoracic and the abdominal segments. Bilateral dendritic arborizations are located in the dorsal anterior region of the metathoracic segment, with axon terminals found in the dorsal abdominal segment.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located between the metathoracic and abdominal neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010). It has bilateral dendritic arbors in the dorsal anterior metathoracic neuromere and axonal arbors in the dorsal abdominal neuromere (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal posterior region of the prothoracic segment. Neurites project medially entering the neuropil through a tract entrance located laterally to the region between the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located dorsoposterior to the prothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects medially entering the neuropil through a tract entrance between the pro- and mesothoracic neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites enter the neuropil via a tract entrance in the dorsal anterior region of the mesothoracic segment. It projects ventromedially and turns back dorsally. Dendritic arbors are located in the dorsal region while the axonal arbors are located in the ventral region of the mesothoracic segment.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body in the dorsal mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et a., 2010). It enters the neuropil in the dorsal anterior mesothoracic neuromere, then projects ventromedially and turns back dorsally (Yu et al., 2010). Dendritic arbors are found dorsally while the axonal arbors are found ventrally (Yu et al., 2010). It is cholinergic (Lillvis et al., 2024). There are approximately 18 of these cells per organism (Lillvis et al., 2024).

definition.value: Mainly studies in males - unclear whether sexually dimorphic.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region of the prothoracic segment, at the midline. A neurite enters the neuropil and projects anteriorly, exiting the VNC.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located on the dorsal midline posterior to the prothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It enters the neuropil and projects anteriorly, exiting the ventral nerve cord (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region between the mesothoracic and metathoracic segments. A neurite enters the neuropil laterally and projects anteriorly.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located at the junction between the dorsal mesothoracic and metathoracic neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010). It projects laterally to enter the neuropil then projects anteriorly (Yu et al., 2010).

Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located at the junction between the dorsal mesothoracic and metathoracic neuromeres, very close dMS4 (Yu et al., 2010). It projects medially towards the midline and turns anteriorly (Yu et al., 2010). Arborization is found in the mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). There is one of these cells per hemisphere and it is cholinergic (Lillvis et al., 2024).

definition.value: No male examples found by Yu et al. (2010). Found in the male by Lillvis et al. (2024).

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region between the mesothoracic and metathoracic segments, close to an entry tract. Neurites project ventrally.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located dorsally between the mesothoracic and metathoracic neuromeres (Yu et al., 2010). It projects ventrally (Yu et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the dorsal region of the metathoracic segment. It projects outs of the abdominal segment.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the dorsal metathoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It has a projection that extends out of the abdominal neuromere (Yu et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the abdominal segment. It projects to the ipsilateral metathoracic neuromere.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located posterior to the metathoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). Its projections innervate the ipsilateral metathoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the midline of the abdominal segment. It projects along the ventral nerve cord to the brain.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Fruitless neuron with its cell body located ventrally on the midline of the abdominal neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects along the dorsal ventral nerve cord and ascends to the brain (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventrolateral region of the mesothoracic segment. It arborizes extensively in the ipsilateral mesothoracic neuromere before exiting the ventral nerve cord to the mesothoracic legs.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the ventral lateral anterior of the mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects posteriorly, arborizing extensively in the ipsilateral mesothoracic neuromere before exiting the ventral nerve cord towards the mesothoracic leg (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventroanterior region of the mesothoracic segment. Its neurite projects dorsally forming thick arbors in the dorsal mesothoracic neuromere. One branch exits the VNC via the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve to innervate direct and indirect flight muscles (basalar muscles and coxal tergal remotor muscles, respectively).

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with a large cell body in the ventral region of the anterior mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects dorsally forming thick arbors in the dorsal mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). One branch exits the ventral nerve cord via the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve to innervate a flight muscle (Yu et al., 2010). Muscles innervated by these neurons include a tergal remotor of coxa indirect flight muscle and the basilar direct flight muscles (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the anteriolateral region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites project medially and slightly posteriorly, bifurcating into an ipsilateral and a contralateral branches that run along close to the midline. Both branches terminate in the prothoracic neuromere possibly connecting to the foreleg afferents. The contralateral branch then exits the ventral nerve cord.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the lateral region of the anterior mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects medially and bifurcates into an ipsilateral and a contralateral branch that run anteriorly close to the midline, with synapses in the prothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). The contralateral branch exits the VNC (Yu et al., 2010).

definition.value: Unclear whether contralateral branch is ascending or peripheral.

value.value: A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventroanterior region of the mesothoracic segment, adjacent to the vMS2 lineage clone. A neurite projects medially and branches. The ipsilateral branch projects anteriorly to the prothoracic neuromere to arborize in the anterior region. The other branch crosses the midline and forms a contralateral arbor in the prothoracic neuromere before projecting to the metathoracic neuromere.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the ventral anterior mesothoracic neuromere, adjacent to the vMS2 neurons (Yu et al., 2010). It projects medially and branches, with ipsilateral and contralateral branches that both arborize in the prothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). The contralateral branch additionally projects posteriorly to the metathoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventromedial region of the anterior mesothoracic segment. The ipsilateral branch projects anteriorly and terminates in the prothoracic neuromere. The other branch crosses the midline and projects posteriorly. The arborization is similar to that of the vMS4 lineage clone.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the ventromedial anterior of the mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects anteriorly and branches, with an ipsilateral branch that arborizes in the prothoracic neuromere and a contralateral branch that projects posteriorly (Yu et al., 2010).
A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located on the midline in the ventroanterior region of the mesothoracic segment. Its neurite projects dorsally.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located on the midline in the ventral anterior of the mesothoracic neuromere and a neurite that projects dorsally (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventroposterior region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites project dorsally and anteriorly to arborize locally in the mesothoracic neuromere. It is similar to the arborization pattern of the vAB1 lineage clone.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located at the ventral posterior region of the mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010). It projects dorsally and anteriorly, then arborizes locally in the ipsilateral mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010).

A clone of neurons in the adult that express fruitless, whose cell bodies are located in the ventral region of the mesothoracic segment. Neurites project dorsally and curves anteriorly. The projection pattern is highly variable between neurons of this clone.

definition.value: These clones were obtained by FLP recombinase, combining a fru[FLP] allele (FBal0248671) and several GAL4 drivers whose expression includes subsets of fruitless neurons (Yu et al., 2010).

value.value: Adult fruitless neuron with its cell body located in the ventral mesothoracic neuromere and arborization in the mesothoracic neuromere (Yu et al., 2010).
